Simpson, a prominent American football player in the 1970s, faced notoriety for the 1994 murders of his ex-wife Nicole Brown-Simpson and Ron Goldman.
Despite being acquitted in a racially charged trial, Simpson was recently arrested in Las Vegas for armed robbery.
He allegedly stole sports memorabilia from a hotel room, leading to multiple felony charges.
Simpson's co-defendants are also facing legal consequences.
The case involves a complex web of events, including plea deals and testimonies.
Simpson's turbulent past continues to haunt him, with ongoing legal battles and public scrutiny.
